      "note_no": "6",
      "note": "Lit., \"the best of creators\". As Tabari points out, the Arabs apply the designation \"creator\" to every artisan (sani') - a usage also current in European languages with reference to the \"creation\" of works of art and imagination. Since God is the only Creator in the real, primary sense of this word, the phrase ahsan al-khaliqin must be understood in this secondary sense of the term khaliq (cf. Taj al-'Arus, art. khalaqa)."
